@pjbgf I've been looking into the above about only having to download go-git-fixtures when it comes to testing but to me it looks like from a go stand point, it doesn't actually seem possible. Go just seems to add everything to go.mod file regardless of being within a *_test.go file or test only package `package common_test`. Go does seem to know its a test only import, you can use following command `go list -json` to find `"TestImports"`.

I think its safe to assume when a binary built it isn't linked despite requiring a download when imported. I did come across a example of using different go.mod files for the final package and one for testing. However, it seems quite hacky. Basically having an external package within same the repository testing your main package with the same repository, which means it only has access to public interfaces that the main packages exports.

I don't know enough about go-git-fixtures but if the data/ being serializable for each test, maybe it could be moved out of repository and downloaded at runtime from a different location when `go test` is run?

