Writing a quick script to scan all the TTL implementations for pins which are set and read from could be a bit more conclusive, but that could also be fooled.

Edit: tried writing the aforementioned script, but turns out the code base is a bit more complicated than I thought, but for the low hanging fruit that my script was able to understand only Ttl7164 calls `getPortValue` with a output port as a param, and that seems to be okay?  I'm not quite sure what `data.pullDown` does though.

Gonna include my script in here anyway (note that it expects to be placed in the root project directory, alongside for example `src`)

<details>

<summary> <code>check_ttl_pindefs.py</code> </summary>

```python
from pathlib import Path
import re

dir = Path(__file__).parent/"src/main/java/com/cburch/logisim/std/ttl"

def main():
	for i in dir.glob("Ttl*.java"):
		if not i.name.removeprefix("Ttl").removesuffix(".java").isnumeric():
			continue
		src = i.read_text()
		consts = {}
		for j in re.finditer(r"public static final (?:byte|int) (\w+) = (\d+);",src):
			consts[j.group(1)] = int(j.group(2))
		decl = re.search(r"super\(\s*.+,\D*(\d+),\s*new\s+byte\s*\[\]\s*{\s*((?:\d+,?\s*)+)},(?:\s*new\s+byte\s*\[\]\s*{((\w+,?\s*)+)})?",src)
		if decl is None:
			# make sure its not a trivial variant...
			if "getPortValue" not in src and "setPort" not in src:
				print("!!!:", i, "seems trivial, skipping...")
				continue
			print("!!!:", i, "cannot find decl")
			continue
		n_pins = int(decl.group(1))
		out_pins = {int(i) for i in re.sub(r"\s*","",decl.group(2)).split(",")}
		in_pins = set(range(1,n_pins+1)) - out_pins
		if decl.group(3) is not None:
			unused_pins = [int(i) if i.isnumeric() else consts[i] for i in re.sub(r"\s*","",decl.group(3)).split(",")]
		else:
			unused_pins = []
		for j in re.finditer(r"\.(setPort|getPortValue)\(([^,)]+)",src):
			if not j.group(2).isnumeric():
				if j.group(2) not in consts:
					print("!!!:", i, "non trivial pin r/w:", j.group(2))
					continue
				pin = consts[j.group(2)]+1
			else:
				pin = int(j.group(2))+1
			if pin >= n_pins//2:  # GND
				pin += 1
			for unused in unused_pins:
				if pin >= unused:
					pin += 1
					if pin == n_pins//2:  # GND
						pin += 1
			write = j.group(1) == "setPort"
			if pin in (in_pins if write else out_pins):
				print("!!!:", i,"input" if write else "output", f"pin ({j.group(2)}={pin}) is","written to" if write else "read from")



if __name__ == "__main__":
	main()
```

</details>

