This looks similar to #33175. 

We won't support it directly for now but we can add a type that you can augment on your side using module augmentation:
```ts
declare module '@mui/material/TextField' {
  interface TextFieldFormHelperTextSlotPropsOverrides {
    'data-cy'?: string;
  }
}
```

But for that the fix would be to support it:
```diff
@@ -50,6 +50,8 @@ export interface TextFieldSlots {
   select: React.ElementType;
 }

+export interface TextFieldFormHelperTextSlotPropsOverrides {}
+
 export type TextFieldSlotsAndSlotProps<InputPropsType> = CreateSlotsAndSlotProps<
   TextFieldSlots,
   {
@@ -77,7 +79,11 @@ export type TextFieldSlotsAndSlotProps<InputPropsType> = CreateSlotsAndSlotProps
      * Props forwarded to the form helper text slot.
      * By default, the available props are based on the [FormHelperText](https://mui.com/material-ui/api/form-helper-text
/#props) component.
      */
-    formHelperText: SlotProps<React.ElementType<FormHelperTextProps>, {}, TextFieldOwnerState>;
+    formHelperText: SlotProps<
+      React.ElementType<FormHelperTextProps>,
+      TextFieldFormHelperTextSlotPropsOverrides,
+      TextFieldOwnerState
+    >;
     /**
      * Props forwarded to the select slot.
      * By default, the available props are based on the [Select](https://mui.com/material-ui/api/select/#props) component
```

As for `htmlInput` slot working, it is because of TextField html input allowing any attributes. See https://github.com/mui/material-ui/issues/33175#issuecomment-1225846695. This is a known inconsistency which is a separate issue.

----

> I just found the same problem exists for `Select` -> `slotProps` -> `input`. It too doesn't allow data-attributes as far as the typings go.

You can augment InputBase input with:
```ts
declare module '@mui/material/InputBase' {
  interface InputBaseComponentsPropsOverrides {
    'data-cy'?: string;
  }
}
```

